    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.43-44_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">43</fw>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    Saint Elizabeth's Day
                    She of the roses
                </note>
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THOMAS S. JONES, JR.
                        <lb/>
                    411 WEST 115TH STREET
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK CITY</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 19, 1929</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear friend,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Sunday afternoon, at a small tea, Dr. Driggs spoke at length of the Oregon Trail. Hamlin Garland was present. Both spoke <hi rend="underline">splendidly</hi> of you. &#8212; I raised my voice in your praise again and again. ---- By the way, Peterson is direct descendent of Sam Houston.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Affectionately</salute>
                
                    <signed>T.S. Jones</signed>
                </closer>
                               
                <postscript>
                    <p>The books have gone to Dr. House.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.43-44_0002"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">44</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    After 5 days, return to
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">NEW RIVER STATE SCHOOL,</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Drawer 999,
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">MONTGOMERY, W. VA.</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    MONTGOMERY W. VA.
                    NOWO
                    8-PM
                    1929
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>2 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES POSTAGE 2 CENTS 2</p>
                </figure>
                
                <note type="recipient">Jones letter</note>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Post-Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Saint Louis</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
